  <span id="freeText17702026490537843122" style="display:none"><i>"I make a story for my life, for each step my brown shoe takes."</i><br /><br />Esperanza Cordero, a Mexican-American girl living in poverty, gives a soaring voice to a multitude of characters who otherwise would remain in darkness all their pitiful lives. Echoing the undying optimism even in the most wretched place, Esperanza stands for sunny days, for light and memories.<br /><br /> In the midst of countless insignificant young adult books, The House On Mango Street is an exception. Awe-inspiring writing with a powerful message duly delivered.</span>
