<span id="freeTextContainer12488786160222689188">I did not care for the style of writing...each small chapter(1.5-2 pgs.)(vignette), is a snippet of what life is like on Mango Street for Esperanza. Tbe idea of these snippets (vignettes) is great, but they never kept my attention or painted a vivid picture for me.<br/>It is not a continuous plot, that keeps you hanging. I&apos;m not used to this style, so it really didnt &quot;grab&quot; me.<br/>I was hoping that throughout the book I would connect with the character or &quot;feel&quot; something...I never did.<br/>I was not impresse</span>
  <span id="freeText12488786160222689188" style="display:none">I did not care for the style of writing...each small chapter(1.5-2 pgs.)(vignette), is a snippet of what life is like on Mango Street for Esperanza. Tbe idea of these snippets (vignettes) is great, but they never kept my attention or painted a vivid picture for me.<br />It is not a continuous plot, that keeps you hanging. I'm not used to this style, so it really didnt "grab" me.<br />I was hoping that throughout the book I would connect with the character or "feel" something...I never did.<br />I was not impressed. It's jut not a writing style I connect with.</span>
