  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/39234163?book_show_action=true">Dec 03, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex" href="/user/show/1772548-alex">Alex</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780679734772" href="/book/show/139253.The_House_on_Mango_Street">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1772548-alex?shelf=deserted-island-must-haves">deserted-island-must-haves</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer39234163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14961264864778383011">I had the opportunity to meet Sandra in one of her book readings and I was so overcome with emotions I was part babbling, part crying and part laughing with joy. I had to thank her because there was finally someone in the literary world that understood me and was able to tell stories that were similar to mine growing up as a Mexican in Chicago. I adore this book because I finally felt like I wasn&apos;t alone! I&apos;ve seen so many stereotypes of hispanic people and I never felt like I identified with an</span>
  <span id="freeText14961264864778383011" style="display:none">I had the opportunity to meet Sandra in one of her book readings and I was so overcome with emotions I was part babbling, part crying and part laughing with joy. I had to thank her because there was finally someone in the literary world that understood me and was able to tell stories that were similar to mine growing up as a Mexican in Chicago. I adore this book because I finally felt like I wasn't alone! I've seen so many stereotypes of hispanic people and I never felt like I identified with any of them. I'm just a simple first-generation Mexican-American girl trying to figure out the balance between my parent's culture and the American one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14961264864778383011" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
